Business Problem
Learning Management Systems (LMS) require a regular feed of employee demographic and organizational data to:

Provision and update user accounts automatically
Assign training curricula based on department, job code, or business unit
Deactivate or terminate LMS accounts when employees become inactive
Maintain accurate org hierarchy for manager-based assignment routing

Oracle Fusion HCM stores this data across a dozen date-effective tables spanning HR Core, Payroll, Fast Formula, and Reference Data. This query consolidates all required LMS fields into a single flat extract row per employee, ready for EIB delivery.

Main row: person + primary assignment + job (SET ID scoped to BU)
    │
    ├── InstitutionID     ← Fast Formula UDT lookup on legal employer
    ├── Department Code   ← Conditional on active/inactive status
    ├── Department Title  ← String parse on department name
    ├── Hire Date         ← MAX period of service start date
    ├── Status            ← Mapped to LMS A/I codes
    ├── Job Code          ← Conditional on active/inactive status
    ├── Job Title         ← String parse on job name
    ├── Custom Field 1    ← Secondary assignment department
    ├── Custom Field 2    ← Secondary assignment job title (regex cleaned)
    ├── Email             ← Work email type W1
    ├── Date of Birth     ← per_persons
    ├── Gender            ← Legislative data
    ├── Supervisor        ← Assignment supervisors table
    ├── FTE               ← Work measures (formatted)
    ├── NPI               ← National identifier (see security note)
    └── Inactive Reason   ← Status mapped to LMS T code

This query generates a workforce demographics extract containing:

Employee identity information
Employment status
Department details
Job details
Supervisor relationships
Work email
FTE information
Hire dates

Functional Area	Purpose
Employee Master Data	Person and assignment information
Organization Structure	Departments and business units
Job Information	Job codes and titles
Employment Status	Active/inactive workforce status
Supervisory Hierarchy	Manager relationships
Workforce Measures	FTE calculations
Contact Information	Work email extraction

-- ============================================================
-- Script: Fusion HCM – LMS Demographics Outbound Extract
--         (EIB / HealthStream Integration)
-- Author: [Your Name]
-- Date:   YYYY-MM-DD (must be after ACE Apprentice acceptance)
-- Target: Oracle Fusion HCM Cloud
-- ============================================================
-- Description:
--   Extracts employee demographic and assignment data formatted
--   for outbound delivery to a Learning Management System (LMS)
--   via Oracle HCM Extracts / EIB (External Integration Bus).
--
--   Key features:
--     - Resolves Institution ID via a Fast Formula User-Defined
--       Table (UDT) keyed on legal employer name
--     - Derives Department Code and Job Code conditionally based
--       on assignment active/inactive status
--     - Includes primary and secondary assignment details
--     - Surfaces FTE, supervisor, work email, hire date, gender,
--       and date of birth for LMS user provisioning
--     - Maps assignment statuses to LMS-specific codes (A/I/T)
--
-- Parameter:
--   :P_BUSINESS_UNIT  VARCHAR2  Required. Business Unit name to scope the extract.
-- ============================================================

SELECT
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Institution ID
    -- Resolved from a User-Defined Table (UDT) that maps
    -- legal employer names to their LMS institution codes.
    -- Uses the most recent period of service to find the
    -- current legal employer, then looks up the abbreviation.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT v.value
        FROM   ff_user_tables              t,
               ff_user_rows_f              r,
               ff_user_columns             c,
               ff_user_columns_tl          c_tl,
               ff_user_column_instances_f  v,
               per_legal_employers         ple,
               per_periods_of_service      ppos
        WHERE  t.user_table_id          = r.user_table_id
        AND    t.user_table_id          = c.user_table_id
        AND    c.user_column_id         = c_tl.user_column_id
        AND    c.user_column_id         = v.user_column_id
        AND    r.user_row_id            = v.user_row_id
        AND    t.base_user_table_name   = '[YOUR_UDT_TABLE_NAME]'      -- Replace with your UDT name
        AND    c_tl.user_column_name    = '[YOUR_UDT_COLUMN_NAME]'     -- Replace with your UDT column
        AND    UPPER(ple.name)          = r.row_low_range_or_name
        AND    ppos.legal_entity_id     = ple.organization_id
        AND    papf.person_id           = ppos.person_id
        AND    ppos.period_of_service_id = (
                   SELECT MAX(ppos2.period_of_service_id)
                   FROM   per_periods_of_service ppos2
                   WHERE  ppos2.person_id = papf.person_id
               )
    )                                                       AS "InstitutionID",

    ppnf.last_name                                          AS "Last Name",
    ppnf.first_name                                         AS "First Name",
    ppnf.middle_names                                       AS "Middle Name",

    -- User ID derived from person number.
    -- SUBSTR(x, 3) removes an org-specific prefix from the number.
    -- Adjust the offset to match your person number format.
    SUBSTR(papf.person_number, 3)                           AS "User ID",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Department Code
    -- When the assignment is ACTIVE: extract the numeric prefix
    -- of the department name (characters before the first space).
    -- When INACTIVE: return a sentinel value recognised by the
    -- LMS as "no department" — adjust to your LMS requirement.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    CASE
        WHEN (
            SELECT pastv.per_system_status
            FROM   per_assignment_status_types_vl pastv
            WHERE  paam.assignment_status_type_id = pastv.assignment_status_type_id
        ) <> 'ACTIVE'
        THEN '99.9999'                                      -- LMS inactive-department sentinel; adjust as needed
        ELSE (
            SELECT SUBSTR(pd.name, 1, INSTR(pd.name, ' ') - 1)
            FROM   per_departments pd
            WHERE  TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pd.effective_start_date AND pd.effective_end_date
            AND    pd.organization_id = paam.organization_id
        )
    END                                                     AS "Department Code",

    -- Department Title: text after the second space in the dept name
    -- Assumes format: "CODE SUBCODE Department Title"
    (
        SELECT SUBSTR(pd.name, INSTR(pd.name, ' ', INSTR(pd.name, ' ') + 1) + 1)
        FROM   per_departments pd
        WHERE  TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pd.effective_start_date AND pd.effective_end_date
        AND    pd.organization_id = paam.organization_id
    )                                                       AS "Department Title",

    -- Most recent hire date across all periods of service
    (
        SELECT TO_CHAR(MAX(ppos.date_start), 'YYYYMMDD')
        FROM   per_periods_of_service ppos
        WHERE  ppos.person_id = papf.person_id
    )                                                       AS "Hire Date",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Status: mapped to LMS codes A (Active) / I (Inactive)
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT CASE
                   WHEN pastv.per_system_status = 'ACTIVE'   THEN 'A'
                   WHEN pastv.per_system_status = 'INACTIVE' THEN 'I'
                   ELSE pastv.per_system_status
               END
        FROM   per_assignment_status_types_vl pastv
        WHERE  paam.assignment_status_type_id = pastv.assignment_status_type_id
    )                                                       AS "Status",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Job Code
    -- When INACTIVE: return zero-padded sentinel for LMS.
    -- When ACTIVE:   return the job code from the job definition.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    CASE
        WHEN (
            SELECT pastv.per_system_status
            FROM   per_assignment_status_types_vl pastv
            WHERE  paam.assignment_status_type_id = pastv.assignment_status_type_id
        ) <> 'ACTIVE'
        THEN '00000'                                        -- LMS inactive-job sentinel; adjust as needed
        ELSE (
            SELECT pjfv.job_code
            FROM   per_jobs_f_vl pjfv
            WHERE  paam.job_id = pjfv.job_id
            AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pjfv.effective_start_date AND pjfv.effective_end_date
        )
    END                                                     AS "Job Code",

    -- Job Title: text after the first " - " separator in the job name
    -- Assumes job name format: "CODE - Job Title Description"
    (
        SELECT SUBSTR(pjfv.name, INSTR(pjfv.name, '-') + 2)
        FROM   per_jobs_f_vl pjfv
        WHERE  paam.job_id = pjfv.job_id
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pjfv.effective_start_date AND pjfv.effective_end_date
    )                                                       AS "Job Title",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Custom Field 1: Secondary assignment department name
    -- Returns the organization name for the most recent active
    -- non-primary assignment (e.g. dual role or secondary position)
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT hou.name
        FROM   per_all_assignments_m          paam1,
               hr_organization_units_f_tl    hou
        WHERE  paam1.person_id              = papf.person_id
        AND    paam1.effective_latest_change = 'Y'
        AND    paam1.primary_flag           != 'Y'
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN paam1.effective_start_date AND paam1.effective_end_date
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN hou.effective_start_date   AND hou.effective_end_date
        AND    paam1.organization_id        = hou.organization_id
        AND    hou.language                 = USERENV('LANG')
        AND    paam1.assignment_status_type = 'ACTIVE'
        ORDER BY paam1.effective_start_date DESC
        FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY
    )                                                       AS "Custom Field 1",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Custom Field 2: Secondary assignment job title
    -- Reformats job name from "CODE.SUB - Title" to "CODE.SUB Title"
    -- using REGEXP_REPLACE to strip the separator for LMS display.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT REGEXP_REPLACE(
                   pjt.name,
                   '^([0-9.]+)[[:space:]]*-[[:space:]]*(.*)$',
                   '\1 \2'
               )
        FROM   per_all_assignments_m  paam1,
               per_jobs_f             pj,
               per_jobs_f_tl          pjt
        WHERE  pj.job_id              = pjt.job_id
        AND    paam1.person_id        = papf.person_id
        AND    paam1.effective_latest_change = 'Y'
        AND    paam1.primary_flag    != 'Y'
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN paam1.effective_start_date AND paam1.effective_end_date
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pj.effective_start_date    AND pj.effective_end_date
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pjt.effective_start_date   AND pjt.effective_end_date
        AND    paam1.job_id           = pj.job_id
        AND    paam1.assignment_status_type = 'ACTIVE'
        AND    pjt.language           = USERENV('LANG')
        ORDER BY paam1.effective_start_date DESC
        FETCH FIRST 1 ROW ONLY
    )                                                       AS "Custom Field 2",

    NULL                                                    AS "Custom Field 3",
    NULL                                                    AS "Custom Field 4",

    -- Work email address (type W1 = primary work email)
    (
        SELECT pea.email_address
        FROM   per_email_addresses pea
        WHERE  papf.person_id = pea.person_id
        AND    pea.email_type = 'W1'
    )                                                       AS "User E-mail address",

    -- Fields required by LMS file spec but sourced externally or not applicable
    NULL                                                    AS "Unique Check ID",
    NULL                                                    AS "Review Date",
    NULL                                                    AS "Time Zone",

    -- Date of birth for LMS user record
    (
        SELECT TO_CHAR(pp.date_of_birth, 'YYYYMMDD')
        FROM   per_persons pp
        WHERE  pp.person_id = papf.person_id
    )                                                       AS "Date of Birth",

    -- Gender from legislative data (country-specific)
    (
        SELECT pplf.sex
        FROM   per_people_legislative_f pplf
        WHERE  papf.person_id = pplf.person_id
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pplf.effective_start_date AND pplf.effective_end_date
    )                                                       AS "Gender",

    NULL                                                    AS "Years of Experience",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Supervisor: returns manager's person number
    -- Resolved via per_assignment_supervisors_f which links
    -- an assignment to its line manager.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT papf_s.person_number
        FROM   per_assignment_supervisors_f  pasf,
               per_all_people_f              papf_s
        WHERE  pasf.person_id    = papf.person_id
        AND    pasf.assignment_id = paam.assignment_id
        AND    pasf.manager_id   = papf_s.person_id
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pasf.effective_start_date   AND pasf.effective_end_date
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN papf_s.effective_start_date AND papf_s.effective_end_date
    )                                                       AS "Supervisor",

    TO_CHAR(paam.effective_start_date, 'YYYYMMDD')         AS "Active Date",
    NULL                                                    AS "Inactive All Accounts",

    -- FTE value from work measures, formatted to 5 decimal places
    (
        SELECT TO_CHAR(pawmf.value, 'FM9990.00000')
        FROM   per_assign_work_measures_f pawmf
        WHERE  pawmf.assignment_id = paam.assignment_id
        AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN pawmf.effective_start_date AND pawmf.effective_end_date
        AND    pawmf.unit = 'FTE'
    )                                                       AS "FTE",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- NPI field: populated from national identifier record.
    -- NOTE: This field is mapped to SSN in the source system.
    -- Mask or remove this column if the downstream LMS does
    -- not require it, or replace with a non-sensitive identifier.
    -- Hyphens are stripped to match LMS expected format.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT REPLACE(pni.national_identifier_number, '-', '')
        FROM   per_national_identifiers pni
        WHERE  papf.person_id            = pni.person_id
        AND    pni.national_identifier_type = 'SSN'        -- Confirm with security team before enabling
    )                                                       AS "NPI",

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Inactive Reason: maps specific inactive user statuses
    -- to the LMS termination code 'T'.
    -- Status names below are examples — verify against your
    -- Fusion instance's configured assignment status labels.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    (
        SELECT CASE
                   WHEN pastv2.user_status IN (
                       'Inactive - Payroll Eligible',
                       'Inactive - No Payroll',
                       'Suspended - No Payroll',
                       'Suspended - Payroll Eligible'
                   ) THEN 'T'
                   ELSE ''
               END
        FROM   per_assignment_status_types_vl pastv2
        WHERE  pastv2.assignment_status_type_id = paam.assignment_status_type_id
    )                                                       AS "Inactive Reason",

    NULL                                                    AS "Inactive Start Date",
    NULL                                                    AS "Inactive End Date",
    NULL                                                    AS "Term Code"

FROM
    per_all_people_f            papf,
    per_person_names_f          ppnf,
    per_all_assignments_m       paam,
    per_jobs_f_vl               pjfv,
    fnd_setid_assignments       fsa,
    fun_all_business_units_v    bu,
    fnd_setid_sets_vl           fs

WHERE
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Core person and assignment joins (date-effective)
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    papf.person_id              = ppnf.person_id
    AND papf.person_id          = paam.person_id
    AND TRUNC(SYSDATE)          BETWEEN papf.effective_start_date AND papf.effective_end_date
    AND TRUNC(SYSDATE)          BETWEEN ppnf.effective_start_date AND ppnf.effective_end_date
    AND TRUNC(SYSDATE)          BETWEEN paam.effective_start_date AND paam.effective_end_date
    AND ppnf.name_type          = 'GLOBAL'
    AND paam.assignment_type    = 'E'       -- Employee assignments only
    AND paam.primary_flag       = 'Y'       -- Primary assignment only

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Job set resolution via Business Unit → Set ID
    -- Ensures job codes are resolved from the correct reference
    -- data set assigned to the specified Business Unit.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    AND paam.job_id             = pjfv.job_id (+)
    AND TRUNC(SYSDATE)          BETWEEN pjfv.effective_start_date AND pjfv.effective_end_date
    AND pjfv.set_id             = fs.set_id
    AND fsa.determinant_type    = 'BU'
    AND fsa.determinant_value   = bu.bu_id
    AND fsa.set_id              = fs.set_id
    AND fsa.reference_group_name = 'PER_JOBS'
    AND bu.bu_name              = :P_BUSINESS_UNIT

    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    -- Latest assignment record per person
    -- Correlated subquery ensures we pick the most recent
    -- effective assignment row, avoiding duplicates when
    -- multiple history rows fall within the current date range.
    -- -------------------------------------------------------
    AND paam.effective_start_date = (
            SELECT MAX(paam2.effective_start_date)
            FROM   per_all_assignments_m paam2
            WHERE  paam2.person_id       = papf.person_id
            AND    paam2.primary_flag    = 'Y'
            AND    paam2.assignment_type = 'E'
            AND    TRUNC(SYSDATE) BETWEEN paam2.effective_start_date AND paam2.effective_end_date
        );


